<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <meta charset="utf-8">
        <title>Word Counter</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h1>Redundancy Check</h1>
        <h3>Have someone you want to impress? Want to seem smarter than you are? If you think you might be overusing a word, enter the phrase below and the word you'd like to check for. We'll let you know if you should invest in a thesaurus...</h3>

        <form id="count-init" action="/count" method="post">
            <input type="text" name="string" placeholder="Enter your text...">
            <input type="text" name="word" value="Enter the word you want to check for...">
            <button type="submit" name="button">Run Check</button>
        </form>
    </body>
</html>
